&lt;h1 id="the-top-of-my-todo-list"&gt;The Top of My Todo List&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;April 2012&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A palliative care nurse called Bronnie Ware made a list of the biggest regrets of the dying. Her list seems plausible. I could see myself — can see myself — making at least 4 of these 5 mistakes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you had to compress them into a single piece of advice, it might be: don&amp;rsquo;t be a cog. The 5 regrets paint a portrait of post-industrial man, who shrinks himself into a shape that fits his circumstances, then turns dutifully till he stops.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>What Doesn't Seem Like Work?</title><link>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/work/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_en/work/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/paul_graham/essays_zh/work/"&gt;中文版&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
